\import{base-macros}
\date{2026-04-06T18:54:24Z}
\tag{public}
\title{Processing in Memory for ML}
\p{Notes on guest lecture by Yufeng Gu titled \em{Architecture and System Co-Design for Scalable Large Language Model Inference}}
\p{TFLOPs increasing much faster than DRAM bandwidth -> Hardware scaling is hitting the \em{memory wall}.}
\p{Data center power consumption also increasing #{\approx} 10\% a year.}
\p{\strong{GPUs are under low utilization for LLM inference}}
\ul{
  \li{Prefix stage: parallel}
  \li{Decoding stage: sequential -> bottleneck!}
}
\p{As batch size increases, the [[TJLA]] dominates memory usage.}
\ul{
  \li{KV cache size grows with context length.}
  \li{Tradeoff between context length and batch size.}
}
\remark{
Unlike fully-connected cannot batch self-attention because it depends on the individual prompts.
}
\p{\strong{Recall:} operational intensity is ##{\frac{\text{compute throughput}}{\text{memory bandwidth}}}}
\p{\strong{Inference much lower operational intensity than GEMM!}}
\ul{
  \li{Inference only doing matrix #{\times} row}
  \li{If embedding dim is #{D}, then this is only #{D} ops / byte.}
}
\p{Processing in memory (PIM) enables faster memory bandwidth.}
\problem{Has lower memory capacity (fewer GB) due to added processing units (PU).
}
\solution{Use Compute eXpress Link (CXL) to do memory expansion to get high memory bandwidth + expend memory capacity.}
\remark{
Put high use operations i.e. vector multiplication, element-wise multiplication in PIM module (99\% usage). Put more complicated operations on PNM accelerator. TODO: ISAs for each specified on slides (not available yet).
}
\remark{
CENT supports inter and intra-device communication via connecting communication controller to shared buffer and CXL port.
}
\p{\strong{Communcation primitives:} multicast and gather}
\ul{
  \li{Multicast: send to all CXL devices.}
  \li{Gather: receive data sequentially from all CXL devices.}
  \li{Multicsat-gather -> tensor parallel.}
}
\p{\em{Peer-to-peer:} can also support pipeline parallelism.}
\remark{
For fast communication, use tensor parallelism i.e. if connected via NVLink. If slower communication use pipeline parallelism. Can mix.
}

\remark{
Longer context -> better performance for PIM (TODO: why?). HBM + PIM does not scale. Cannot arbitrarily add PIM.
}
